column13: Electronic components utilize the waste areas (14) of panelized circuit boards (12) to provide self-fixturing of the components (10) to the circuit boards prior to soldering. The components (10), connectors in particular, include a main body or housing (18) intended to remain with the circuit board (12) after assembly and one or more locator tabs (20) extending from the housing (18) into the waste area or areas (14) of the panelized circuit board (12). A weakened area (22) located between the housing (18) and the locator tab (20) facilitates separation of the locator tab (20) from the housing (18) and permits the locator tab or tabs (29) to be easily removed at the same time the waste area (14) of the circuit board is removed from the useful area.

column12: ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR WITH LATCH TO RETAIN IC CARD
column13: AN ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR (10) INCLUDES A LATCH FOR RETAINING AN IC CARD. A CARD ADAPTOR BODY RECEIVES THE IC CARD. THE ADAPTOR BODY HAS A CONNECTOR END INCLUDING A PIN HEADER (28). A PAIR OF OPPOSED CARD SIDE EDGE GUIDES (38,40)EXTEND FROM THE CONNECTOR END AND TERMINATE ADJACENT AN OPEN END OF THE ADAPTOR BODY. THE IC CARD IS INSERTED INTO THE ADAPTOR BODY AND HAS A CONNECTOR EDGE ENGAGED WITH THE PIN HEADER, A PAIR OF OPPOSED SIDES ENGAGED WITH THE SIDE EDGE GUIDES AND A REAR EDGE AT THE OPEN END OF THE ADAPTOR BODY. A RETAINER (16) INCLUDES A FLEXIBLE ARM (18)AND A HOOK EXTENDING FROM THE CONNECTOR END INTO THE OPEN END. THE HOOK IS AUTOMATICALLY ENGAGED WITH THE CARD REAR EDGE WHEN THE CARD IS INSERTED FOR RETAINING THE CARD ENGAGED WITH THE PIN HEADER, AND IS MOVABLE OUT OF ENGAGEMENT WITH THE CARD REAR EDGE TO PERMIT THE CARD TO BE REMOVED FROM THE ADAPTOR BODY.FIGURE 1

column13: AN ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR IS PROVIDED FOR USE WITH A CIRCUIT CARD (10) WHICH HAS A GENERALLY PLANAR SUBSTRATE (42) HAVING MULTIPLE CONDUCTIVE ELEMENTS DISPOSED ALONG AT LEAST ONE EDGE THEREOF. EACH OF THE CONDUCTIVE ELEMENTS IS COUPLED TO AN ELECTRICALLY CONDUCTIVE TRACE (46) ON THE SURFACE OF THE PLANAR SUBSTRATE (42), AND AT LEAST ONE CONDUCTIVE COVER PANEL 52;54) IS PROVIDED WHICH MAY BE MOUNTED TO THE PLANAR SUBSTRATE. AN ELECTRICAL COUPLING (30) WHICH INCLUDES MULTIPLE ELECTRICAL CONTACTS (32) FOR EXTERNAL CONNECTION TO THE CIRCUIT CARD (10) IS PROVIDED AND EACH OF THE MULTIPLE ELECTRICAL CONTACTS (32) IS THEN COUPLED TO AN ASSOCIATED ELECTRICAL TERMINAL, SUCH AS A SOLDER TAIL, WHICH MAY THEN BE MATED TO ONE OF THE MULTIPLE CONDUCTIVE ELEMENTS ON THE PLANAR SUBSTRATE (42). A GROUNDING CLIP (38) IS THEN MOUNTED ON AT LEAST ONE OF THE ASSOCIATED ELECTRICAL TERMINALS (36). THE GROUNDING CLIP (38) INCLUDES A CONDUCTIVE MEMBER (56) WHICH EXTENDS OUTWARD FROM THE ELECTRICAL TERMINAL TO ENGAGE THE GENERALLY PLANAR CONDUCTIVE COVER PANEL (52;54)WHILE THE CONDUCTIVE COVER PANEL (52;54) IS MOUNTED ABOVE THE SUBSTRATE SUCH THAT AT LEAST ONE ELECTRICALLY CONDUCTIVE TRACE (46) ON THE PLANAR SUBSTRATE IS ELECTRICALLY COUPLED THROUGH A CONDUCTIVE ELEMENT (58), THE ELECTRICAL COUPLING (30) AND THE GROUNDING CLIP (38) TO THE CONDUCTIVE COVER PANEL (52;54). IN THIS MANNER, A CONDUCTIVE TRACE (46) WITHIN THE CIRCUIT CARD (10) MAY BE SIMULTANEOUSLY GROUNDED THROUGH THE EXTERNAL ELECTRICAL CONTACTS (32) OF THE COUPLING (30) AND TO THE CONDUCTIVE COVER PANEL (52;54), MINIMIZING THE POSSIBLE DISCHARGE OF AN ELECTRICAL CHARGE AND PREVENTING ELECTROMAGNETIC EMISSIONS BY THE CIRCUIT CARD (10).
